Prepare rice according to package directions. Meanwhile, wash hands. Sprinkle chicken with salt. Wash hands. Melt 2 tablespoons butter in large nonstick skillet over medium-high. Brown chicken on both sides, about 3 minutes per side. Transfer to plate. Add remaining butter to skillet, reduce heat to medium and cook onion 5 minutes or until soft. Stir in curry powder. Cook 1 minute. Return chicken to skillet; add apple, raisins and broth. Bring to boil; cover, reduce heat to medium-low and cook 10 to 12 minutes or until chicken is done (internal temp 170 degrees F).